  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable access to and use of community services for the prevention and treatment of malaria in Segou and Mopti regions</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving access to and use of preventive and treatment services available for 19,650 members of the community health solidarity fund (FSSC in French) through financial mobilization, coordination and effective and sustainable management of funds.

 Strengthen early care for suspected cases of malaria and intermittent preventive treatment taken by 375,750 people through targeted behavior change communication activities, coordination and advocacy, and the connecting vulnerable target communities to health centers.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Its goal is to establish a sustainable system for responding to the demand for access to and use of preventive services and malaria control in Bandiagara, Mopti and Niono, Segou.</narrative>
  </description>
